Schematic representation of the infraciliature of (A) the ventrum, and (B) the dorsum of the cell, as seen after silver-carbonate impregnation. Note that the ventral surface has been drawn to show clearly the dierent parts of the infraciliatureÐfor this purpose the caudal pole of the cell is slightly shifted towards the reader in order to show the arrangement of the caudal cilia around the pole. PO1, PO2, paroral kineties. PK, oral polykinetid. L1, L2, L3, argentiferous longitudinal lines that separate the silver-impregnated ribs supporting the cytostome. CC, caudal cilia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[86,1042,1353,1696]" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">
The contractile vacuole is at the posterior end of the cell, but its pore could not be observed. The argyrome was not observed. The macronucleus is ellipsoidal (some macronuclei measured on silver-carbonate specimens were 36Ö 
<quantity box="[828,874,1417,1441]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" unit="m" value="38.0">
38 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,874,1417,1441]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m, 29Ö 
<quantity box="[967,1012,1417,1441]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" unit="m" value="32.0">
32 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[998,1012,1417,1441]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m, 
<geoCoordinate box="[86,159,1449,1473]" degrees="23.5" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" precision="5555" value="-23.5">23.5 Ö</geoCoordinate>
<quantity box="[160,205,1449,1473]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" unit="m" value="35.0">
35 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[191,205,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m), and located at the posterior end of the cell (®gures 18±21) There is one micronucleus (6Ö 
<quantity box="[346,378,1481,1505]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" unit="m" value="6.0">
6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[364,378,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m, 7 
<geoCoordinate box="[431,489,1481,1505]" degrees="3.5" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" precision="5555" value="-3.5">Ö3.5</geoCoordinate>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[494,508,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">m</emphasis>
m) above it.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[86,1042,1353,1696]" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis box="[127,213,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Esteban &amp; Finlay &amp; Olmo &amp; Tyler" authorityYear="2000" box="[228,461,1513,1537]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Lembadionidae" genus="Lembadion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Hymenostomatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="subSpecies" species="embadion" subSpecies="curvatum">
<emphasis box="[228,461,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">L embadion curvatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a benthic ciliateÐit was found among sediment particles, in fresh water (Lake Bantic), feeding on 
<taxonomicName box="[739,898,1545,1569]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Cyclidiidae" genus="Cristigera" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[739,849,1545,1569]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Cristigera</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(®gure 16), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1952" box="[86,406,1577,1601]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Cinetochilidae" genus="Cinetochilum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Hymenostomatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="margaritaceum">
<emphasis box="[86,406,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Cinetochilum margaritaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and on small ¯agellates. Other ciliate species observed in the same samples were: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Penard, 1922)" baseAuthorityName="Penard" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[389,778,1609,1633]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Loxocephalidae" genus="Balanonema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="biceps">
<emphasis box="[389,601,1609,1633]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Balanonema biceps</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PENARD, E." box="[620,769,1609,1633]" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" refId="ref13350" refString="PENARD, E., 1922, E A tudes sur les Infusoires d'eau Douce (GeneAve)." type="book" year="1922">Penard, 1922</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[795,1042,1609,1633]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Loxocephalidae" genus="Dexiotricha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis box="[795,1042,1609,1633]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Dexiotricha granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion box="[99,155,1641,1664]" country="United Kingdom" name="Kent" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Kent</collectingRegion>
, 1881), 
<taxonomicName authority="Kahl, 1928" authorityName="Kahl" authorityYear="1928" box="[268,610,1641,1665]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Cyclidiidae" genus="Cristigera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[268,461,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Cristigera media</emphasis>
Kahl, 1928
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[634,794,1641,1665]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Cyclidiidae" genus="Cristigera" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[634,744,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Cristigera</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[817,1034,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">
Cyclidium 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cohn" authorityYear="1866" box="[945,1034,1641,1665]" class="Colpodea" family="Cyrtolophosididae" genus="Cyrtolophosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtolophosidida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="citrullus">citrullus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. F. MuEller" baseAuthorityYear="1773" box="[86,312,1672,1696]" class="Spirotrichea" family="Halteriidae" genus="Halteria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Oligotrichida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="grandinella">
<emphasis box="[86,312,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Halteria grandinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="ClapareAde and Lachmann, 1859" authorityName="ClapareAde and Lachmann" authorityYear="1859" box="[379,936,1671,1696]" class="Prostomatea" family="Prorodontidae" genus="Urotricha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Prostomatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="farcta">
<emphasis box="[379,562,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="171">Urotricha farcta</emphasis>
ClapareÁde and Lachmann, 1859
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5279482" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5279482" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5279482/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="172" startId="15.[86,102,1510,1531]" targetBox="[105,1007,147,1477]" targetPageId="15">
